<h2>Discord Webhooks</h2>
<p>Discord Webhooks are also supported by the Star Citizen Gimp bot. <a asp-area="" asp-controller="Home" asp-action="DiscordWebhooks">Click here to register</a> a Discord Webhook which will allow Star Citizen Gimp to push notifications to a channel on your Discord Server.</p>
<h2>Security &amp; Privacy</h2>
<p>We take security very seriously and do our best to protect your email address;</p>
<ul>
    <li>The site supports SSL, so when you submit your email address it is encrypted and it is also protected by CSRF to make sure it is not intercepted or submitted by someone else.</li>
    <li>Your email address is also encrypted on the datastore level which only the website and the bot has access to and it only decrypts the email addresses when sending notifications when updates are detected.</li>
    <li>No data is shared to any 3rd parties other than Google for analytics as per our privacy policy.</li>
</ul>
<h4>Recommentations for the super paranoid</h4>
<p>If you are extremely paranoid then you can also consider not using your main email address (the one that you use for Star Citizen) and rather use a new alias or address that gets forwarded to your main address.</p>
<p>Alternatively there is also a very early console version of the bot that can be run locally and the source code can be found <a href="https://github.com/scgimp/scgimp-bot">here</a> for those who don't trust anything (what are you even doing on the internet, DANGER DANGER Will Robinson!?) or those who want to modify and extend it for their own use.</p>
<h2>Toubleshooting</h2>
<p>If you are not receiving email notifications make sure that you subscribed with the correct email address and that the sender address noreply@scgimp.com is whitelisted and does not end up in in your junk folder. If you are still stuck you are welcome to send an email to <a href="mailto:scgimp@ioflux.co.za">scgimp@ioflux.co.za</a> for technical support and we will see if we can help you.</p>
